description:
[]quote]Quirky 6.1.1 released

Quirky is my fun project to explore new ideas for Linux

In a nutshell, Quirky6 is intended to be as small as possible (hence compiled from source in T2), very fast, very simple, optimised to run on Flash memory media, and very quirky. There are other extended ideas that are in the pipeline.

Quirky 6.1.1 is a bugfix release of 6.1. 

Please see Announcement, Release Notes, and install instructions in the 'quirky-6.1' folder:  &lt;a href=&quot;
http://distro.ibiblio.org/quirky/quirky6/x86/quirky-6.1/release-Quirky-6.1.htm&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot; target=&quot;_NEW&quot;&gt;
http://distro.ibiblio.org/quirky/quirky6/x86/quirky-6.1/release-Quirky-6.1.htm&lt;/a&gt; 

...except of course, you download the files from the 'quirky-6.1.1' folder:  &lt;a href=&quot;
http://distro.ibiblio.org/quirky/quirky6/x86/quirky-6.1.1/&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot; target=&quot;_NEW&quot;&gt;
http://distro.ibiblio.org/quirky/quirky6/x86/quirky-6.1.1/&lt;/a&gt; 

Quirky 6.1.1 has many important bug fixes, it is highly recommended to use. 

If you already have an earlier version than 6.1.1 installed, there are Service Packs, an easy means to upgrade.[/quote]

more at [url]http://bkhome.org/news/?viewDetailed=00038[/url]

release date 5 jan 2013
